The All Progressives Congress (APC) Professional Council has appealed to delegates to ensure the party’s primary election processes are free and fair. Director-General Oluseyi Bamigbade, who addressed reporters yesterday in Lagos, said the delegates are expected to ensure the exercises are carried out in accordance with the APC constitution to avoid rancour. Bamigbade also praised the APC National Chairman, Abdullahi Adamu, for a well-planned primary election, saying he has confidence in the Adamu leadership to deliver a hitch-free primary election.   Sule declares for second term     Journalist gives uniforms to alma mater     Ogbomoso Club chief to Nigerians: help build communities   He advised Nigerians to ensure they get their Permanent Voters Card (PVC) ready for the 2023 general election. “The power of Nigerians to get their dream country is in their hands. They should get their PVC’s ready. Their future is now,” he added. Bamigbade also congratulated the Muslim faithful for enjoying the grace to partake in Ramadan. He also thanked them for using the period to seek the face of Allah in efforts to make the country a better place to live.